            <title>[CASSANDRA-13525] ReverseIndexedReader may drop rows during 2.1 to 3.0 upgrade</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-13525</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;During an upgrade from 2.1 (or 2.2) to 3.0 (or 3.x) queries which perform reverse iteration may silently drop rows from their results. This can happen before sstableupgrade is run and when the sstables are indexed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
